<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com">
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.0-beta3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
    integrity="sha384-eOJMYsd53ii+scO/bJGFsiCZc+5NDVN2yr8+0RDqr0Ql0h+rP48ckxlpbzKgwra6" crossorigin="anonymous">
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:ital,wght@0,100;0,300;0,400;0,700;1,100;1,400&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">

  <title>Time Clock</title>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">

    <div class="row d-none site-heading">
      <div class="col">
        <h3 class="mt-5 mb-5 text-center display-5">Site: San Jose Site</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="button-container">
      <button onclick="bgButtonClickHandler('clockInTime');" class="button bg-button button-start-shift"
        data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal">Start
        Shift</button>
      <button onclick="bgButtonClickHandler('clockOutTime');" class="button bg-button button-end-shift"
        data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal">End Shift</button>
      <button onclick="bgButtonClickHandler('breakStartTime');" class="button bg-button button-start-break"
        data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal">Start
        Break</button>
      <button data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal" onclick="bgButtonClickHandler('breakEndTime');"
        class="button bg-button button-end-break">End Break</button>
    </div>
    <table class="table my-5 d-none">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Name</th>
          <th scope="col">PIN</th>
          <th scope="col">Start Shift</th>
          <th scope="col">End Shift</th>
          <th scope="col">Shift Break Start</th>
          <th scope="col">Shift Break End</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>

      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="instructions mt-5">
      <ol>
        <li>
          Click 1 of the 4 action buttons above
          <ul>
            <li>Enter your employee PIN</li>
            <li>Share your location (click 'Yes' or 'Allow' whenever prompted, <a href="#">detailed instructions</a>)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Confirm that you have started a shift or a shift break!</strong> When you have an active shift, your
          name will show up below along with details about your shift
        </li>
        <li>
          Review shift & notices for 1) <a href="#">unpaid breaks</a> & 2) <a href="#">overtime</a> below
          <ul>
            <li>Notices will be sent via email/text 30, 15, and 5 minutes to a key deadline (only if email address/phone
              number have been provided)</li>
            <li>Any earned paid breaks given this <a href="#">schedule</a> are your responsibility to take (there are no
              notices or alerts; if not taken, they are voluntarily waived)</li>
            <li>Don't do any work on your break</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p class="small font-weight-bold"><strong>If anything is not working, please email what you were trying to do to
          chronically.team@gmail.com so we can
          manually adjust</strong></p>
    </div>

  </div>
  <footer>
    <div class="container">

      <p class="small">
        ***This calculator is currently designed to support California-based employers. It is built to be simple & cover
        the vast majority of workshifts in a regular day on a standard workweek (as opposed to <a href="#">alternative
          workweeks</a>).
        This implies a few rules & disclaimers below, which should be the employers' responsibility to review with their
        staff
      </p>
      <ul class="small">
        <li><strong>Overtime</strong> - Calculator triggers alerts & reports overtime based on the first column of the
          following overtime
          schedule. In other words, calculator ignores workweek-based calculations, these may require manager to
          manually adjust</li>
        <li><strong>Unpaid breaks</strong>(or meal breaks) - Calculator triggers alerts & reports when a break is
          missed based on the following unpaid breaks schedule. This calculator does not account for waivers; if you
          have implemented waivers, you should just ignore the alerts & reported missing breaks</li>
        <li><strong>Unpaid breaks are strictly enforced</strong> A shift cannot be ended until unpaid breaks are taken
          in accordance with above rule. Given this rule, there are no restrictions to shift or shift break starts and
          ends (i.e., an employee can take a shift break and thereafter immediately end their shift, to meet unpaid
          break requirement). If you have implemented waivers, please email chronically.team@gmail.com when you want to
          manually end a shift</li>
        <li><strong>Paid breaks</strong>(or rest breaks) - Calculator allows breaks to be reported as payable given the
          following paid breaks schedule. Because calculator is designed for flexible scheduling, it further assumes the
          minimum number of breaks are paid and only the first 10 minutes. If no paid breaks are taken, it is assume
          that the employee is voluntarily waiving them</li>
        <li><strong>Split shifts</strong>- Since split shifts don't affect overtime, the time between shifts could be
          entered as a long break. However, since calculator doesn't reflect rates, any split shift premiums would
          require manual calculation</li>
        <li>
          This calculator is a project of Catchbright, LLC and does not constitute legal or HR advice. The calculator &
          the broader Chronically web app only collects & reports time data in accordance with the stated rules above.
          It does not collect hourly rates, wage data, or provide any kind of payroll services. Therefore, it is the
          employers' responsibility to ensure that employees are following appropriate practices and paid in accordance
          with all laws at any jurisdiction. Neither Catchbright, LLC, nor any of its affiliates can be held liable for
          any improper calculations or payments of any kind.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </footer>
  <div class="modal fade" id="exampleModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog">
      <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header">
          <h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLabel">Enter your information</h5>
          <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
          <div class="input-group mb-3">
            <input type="text" id="nameInput" class="form-control" placeholder="Your Name" aria-label="your name">
          </div>
          <div class="input-group mb-3">
            <input type="text" id="PIN" class="form-control" placeholder="Your PIN" aria-label="pin">
          </div>
          <div class="input-group mb-3">
            <input type="text" id="siteLinkInput" class="form-control" placeholder="Site Link" aria-label="siteLink">
          </div>
          <div class="input-group mb-3">
            <input type="text" id="siteNameInput" class="form-control" placeholder="Site Name" aria-label="site name">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
          <button type="button" id="confirmBtn" disabled class="btn btn-primary">Confirm</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.9.1/dist/umd/popper.min.js"
    integrity="sha384-SR1sx49pcuLnqZUnnPwx6FCym0wLsk5JZuNx2bPPENzswTNFaQU1RDvt3wT4gWFG"
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.0-beta3/dist/js/bootstrap.min.js"
    integrity="sha384-j0CNLUeiqtyaRmlzUHCPZ+Gy5fQu0dQ6eZ/xAww941Ai1SxSY+0EQqNXNE6DZiVc"
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/moment.js/2.29.1/moment.min.js"
    integrity="sha512-qTXRIMyZIFb8iQcfjXWCO8+M5Tbc38Qi5WzdPOYZHIlZpzBHG3L3by84BBBOiRGiEb7KKtAOAs5qYdUiZiQNNQ=="
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <script src="/js/employee.js"></script>
</body>

</html>